  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ACE Africa (UK) Institutional assessment and strengthening</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the county of Bungoma in Western Kenya, HIV rates are very high. It lies on the Trans-Africa Highway, with stop-over towns used by long distance truck drivers. Truck drivers are one of the population groups at greater risk of getting HIV, as they travel around a lot and may have many sexual partners.&#xA0; ACE Africa has worked in Bungoma since 2004 and is expanding to four new areas. It will also expand its work with people who are at risk of getting HIV. The project will continue to protect vulnerable children, provide care, training and support for people living with HIV, and make sure the whole community can grow crops and is well fed. The main focus will be to improve the quality of local services, working closely with the local government, so services can continue successfully without needing further grants.</narrative>
  </description>
